I’m amped you’ve decided to focus on mastering Electric-type Pokémon!
As I said, there’s quite a surge of them in the vicinity. I wonder how strong of a current they could all make together!
Just thinking about it makes the hairs on my arm stand up. Or maybe that’s just the static electricity in the air?
Let’s go see these Pokémon in action! Chaaaaarge!
You’re wired for this, %PLAYERNAME%! Now how about spending some quality time with your new friends?
Spark spends as much time as he can with his Pokémon. His instinct for bonding with Electric types is always spot on!
And remember—if you encounter mighty Pokémon out there, try using GO Safari Balls!
Welcome back, %PLAYERNAME%! I’m sure your Electric-type pals were ec-static to spend time with you.
Did you get a chance to battle with them? Electric-type Pokémon are quite strong against Flying and Water types.
But do you know what they’re weak against? Why don’t you spend some more time with them and think on it.
I can corroborate your findings when you come back!
Great job! You’re fully plugged in when it comes to Electric-type Pokémon! Have you thought about their weaknesses?
Here’s a hint: that Golem you caught will be very effective against an Electric type.
That’s grounds for celebration—you’ve got it! Electric-type Pokémon are weak against Ground types. You could say they zap the energy from our high-voltage friends.
Why don’t you roll out your Golem against some Electric types and see for yourself?
As a memento of your Electric mastery, take this medal! I couldn’t be more proud.
Keep that spark alive, and it will continue to take you far.
With so many new Electric-type Pokémon by your side, I’m sure you’ll keep each other amped up for years to come.
Now, I’ve got just a few things left I could use your help with. Let’s finish strong!
Hey, %PLAYERNAME%! Good to see you. How’s your training going?
I’ve been thinking. With all there is to learn, how does a person know when they’ve mastered something?
Just a little food for thought. Anyway, did you notice anything interesting out there?
I was struck by the high number of Electric- and Poison-type Pokémon buzzing and bubbling about.
In fact, speaking of measuring mastery—this is an excellent opportunity!
This is your chance to put your training to the test! Which path will you take to prove your prowess?
All right! You’ve picked your poison! Er, Poison type, that is.
They say you should avoid toxic people, but learning about Poison-type Pokémon is sure to be both fun AND useful!
A challenge you’re ready for, I have no doubt.
Why don’t you start by collecting data on the Poison-type Pokémon in the area.
Just look at all the Poison-type Pokémon you’ve caught. And what excellent snapshots!
I’m confident you could also master Pokémon photography. You should give it a shot!
Ahem. Now that you’ve caught some Poison-type Pokémon, it’s time to get to know them better.
Sharing some Berries is an effective way to build your friendship. Let me know how it goes!
Excellent work, %PLAYERNAME%! You and your Poison-type Pokémon look like great pals already.
Poison types are especially strong against Fairy- and Grass-type Pokémon, but do you know what their weakness is?
Here’s a hint: these Pokémon may “soil” a Poison-type Pokémon’s victory!
Heh. You work on that, and I’ll work on getting some new material. You’ve got this!
Venom...denim? No, that—ah! %PLAYERNAME%! I certainly wasn’t practicing my puns. Anyway, your Poison types are looking stronger than ever!
I wouldn’t want to face off against your team. That is, unless I knew what they were weak against. Any ideas?
Poison-type Pokémon are weak against both Psychic and Ground types, and your Golem has ground covered!
Why don’t you take it out for a spin and see for yourself? Let’s rock and roll!
Please, take this medal as a token of your mastery of Poison types. I couldn’t be more proud.
Your skills are as potent as the Poison-type Pokémon you’re training.
With your guidance, they’ll be the bane of any Pokémon they battle.
Now, I’ve got just a few more research items on the agenda. I know I can count on you!
Can you believe the surge of Electric-type Pokémon in the vicinity?

I just have a few odds and ends left for you, %PLAYERNAME%. Let’s finish strong!
You did it! I just knew you’d master both Poison- and Electric-type Pokémon.
And you even caught a Dynamax Toxtricity—wow! Did you know that it has an electrical organ on its chest?
While generating electricity, it fills its surroundings with what sounds like the strumming of a bass guitar.
Every rockstar needs their rest, though. You’ve earned it. Until next time!
Today is the beginning of a great adventure for you, %PLAYERNAME%.
I’m sure you’ve noticed that there are oodles of Electric- and Poison-type Pokémon appearing in the area.
It’s no easy task, but I believe you have what it takes to master both types—now’s your chance to put your training to the test!

Some Trainers might shy away from confronting Poison-type Pokémon, but not you, %PLAYERNAME%!
And so, with that in mind, I’d like you to collect data on the Poison types in the area—a challenge I’m sure you’re up for!

Your skills are as potent as the Poison-type Pokémon you’re training!
With your guidance, they’ll be the most toxic Pokémon in the world. I mean, in a good way!
I just have a few more odds and ends I could use your help with. I know you can do it!
I have something exciting to show you. This, my friend, is a GO Safari Ball.
Take note—they’re not like normal Poké Balls! They don’t last forever, so you need to use them before they disappear.
They should be useful if you come across any exceptionally strong Pokémon. Try them out and report back!
Welcome back, %PLAYERNAME%! Did you find anything interesting?
And me? I’m glad you asked! I’ve spotted some unusually powerful Pokémon roaming about.
These mighty Pokémon are fully evolved, are larger and stronger than most other Pokémon of their species, and are more challenging to catch.
If you can find some of these mighty Pokémon, GO Safari Balls should be a big help.
Let’s work together to investigate. What a wild adventure this ought to be!

Ah, %PLAYERNAME%, j’ai des nouvelles ! Les chefs de la Team GO Rocket, Arlo, Cliff et Sierra, ont été aperçus dans la région.
Nous ne savons pas encore quels sont leurs plans pour le phénomène Dynamax, mais quels qu’ils soient, ces trois-là les mettront à exécution !
Suis-les et découvre ce qu’ils préparent. Et arrête-les, si nécessaire !
Je suis en train de préparer la suite des opérations. Je pense que j’aurai quelque chose d’ici à ce que tu leur aies réglé leur compte. Bonne chance !
Il semblerait que mes soupçons se soient confirmés : le big boss, Giovanni, est impliqué.
Nous devons mettre fin à ses agissements et je sais que tu es la personne idéale pour cela !
Va lui montrer ce que tu as dans le ventre !
Excellent travail ! Je n’aurais pas pu faire mieux moi-même !
Je connais bien la Team GO Rocket et je sais que nous n’en avons pas fini avec eux, mais tu leur as vraiment mis des bâtons dans les roues.
Je veux jeter un œil aux Pokémon Dynamax à proximité. Est-ce que tu peux t’occuper des Sbires de la Team GO Rocket qui traînent encore dans les parages ?
Bon travail, %PLAYERNAME% ! Les Pokémon Dynamax sont maintenant en sécurité, grâce à ton courage et à tes compétences.
Nous devrons cependant garder un œil sur la Team GO Rocket pendant que nous poursuivons nos recherches sur le phénomène Dynamax.
C’est sans doute mon intuition de professeur, mais j’ai le sentiment qu’une découverte gigantesque est sur le point d’être faite.
%PLAYERNAME% ! J’ai une nouvelle ÉNORME à t’annoncer !
Nous avons trouvé des Pokémon encore plus impressionnants et il semblerait même qu’ils aient changé d’apparence !
De nombreuses questions restent sans réponse, mais heureusement je peux compter sur ton expertise !
Je vais me plonger dans les recherches. Pendant ce temps, je voudrais que tu enquêtes sur le terrain. Avec ton aide, je suis sûr que nous éluciderons ce mystère de taille !
%PLAYERNAME%, j’ai de grandes nouvelles ! Selon mes recherches, il semblerait que nous soyons en présence du phénomène Gigamax.

Les Pokémon gigamaxés ont non seulement une taille et une apparence différentes, mais ils sont également capables d’utiliser une nouvelle attaque. Cette nouvelle attaque semble être unique à une espèce donnée de Pokémon Gigamax.
Nous devons rassembler davantage d’informations sur ces Pokémon aux Sources d’Énergie. C’est une entreprise de taille, mais je sais que tu es à la hauteur.
Je vais continuer mes recherches au laboratoire pendant que tu poursuis ton enquête !
Durant ton absence, une personne parmi mes collègues Professeurs a confirmé mon hypothèse : nous avons bien affaire au phénomène Gigamax !
Imagine un peu toutes les incroyables nouvelles formes de Pokémon que nous allons découvrir ! Les possibilités sont aussi vastes que les Pokémon eux-mêmes ! J’en ai des frissons !
Nous avons encore tellement à découvrir, et je suis ravi de t’avoir comme partenaire de recherche !
%PLAYERNAME%, je suis content de te voir. J’ai reçu de nombreux rapports faisant état d’apparitions de la Team GO Rocket !
Ces fauteurs de troubles préparent quelque chose, j’en suis sûr.
Fais-moi part de tes découvertes et je te tiendrai au courant de mon côté. Et tiens-toi sur tes gardes !
Content de voir que tu es de retour. J’ai étudié les rapports sur la Team GO Rocket et je crois avoir trouvé ce qu’ils manigancent.
Ils sembleraient qu’ils essaient de profiter du phénomène Dynamax.
Tu images le chaos s’ils parvenaient à mettre la main sur une telle puissance ? Nous ne pouvons pas les laisser faire !
Empêche la Team GO Rocket de mettre la main sur des Pokémon Dynamax !
